Story:Lord Bafford inherits a gift-a mechanist servant.  A few months later, the town is stirred with rumors of Lord Bafford's extreme wealth, and more importantly,  Where did he get it?\par
A violent gang of thieves and  thugs abducted Lord Bafford's Servant, and girlf friend with extorsion in mind.  They will  stop at nothing to extort Bafford's secret to wealth.  Lord Bafford has beefed up security, as he plans on keeping his tremendous fortune.  Maybe his throne room will be of actual use to him someday ?  His eventual plan is to buy the city, and then the surrounding territories.  With wealth comes problems, and of course corruption.  With great wealth comes the burden of keeping it.  I have no problem with helping him to lose it.\par
\par
 A city watchman caught me pinching a key, and I was thrown in jail.  No problem, I will just escape and find out what secrets Lord Bafford is keeping. Sometimes rumors can be valuable.\par
 Lord Bafford usually keeps journals, and probably has a book of secrets somewhere.  Hopefully I can find it before the local thieves do.  Maybe in his bedroom, or perhaps in one of his many   counting rooms ?  Time to get going, as even rich men like Lord Bafford can lose all that he holds dear to him in just one night.\par
\par
The idea behind the story: This being based on the first mission in the Dark Project, was also my first love.  At the end of all things since "Return to Bafford Manor" TG, I close my fm hobby.\par
As soon as I can say, I am blind, but can see, I will return to this hobby someday, or maybe not.   Long Live Thief !  My plan just a few months ago was to revise all 16 of my fms using New Dark, but the dream has been lost.  I sincerely thank everyone in TTLG, and Shalebridge Cradle, and Thiefmissions, and Brethren at SouthQuarter for their devotion to a game I have loved for years.  Now you see me, now you dont would have made a great story, but the later has come.  Good bye everyone !\par
